        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">CD refers to John Wood, and his letter of 11 April 1871. For other communications on the platysma myoides, see the <ref target="./DCP-LETT-7615.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter to P. B. Mason, 24 March [1871]</ref>, the <ref target="./DCP-LETT-7657.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from Hubert Airy, 3 April 1871</ref>, and the <ref target="./DCP-LETT-7661.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from John Wood, 6 April 1871</ref>. CD called motion of the platysma purely involuntary in <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_1966.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Descent</hi></ref> 1: 19 (first and second printings).</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">CD’s letter to Wood has not been found, but Wood replied in his letter of 11 April 1871.</note>
